WEBVTT

1
00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:49.400
Who are you?

2
00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:51.030
U-Uh...

3
00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:53.530
My name is Sasaki.

4
00:01:53.530 --> 00:01:56.280
Yeah? Sasaki-san?

5
00:01:56.910 --> 00:01:59.450
You're trespassing. I'm reporting you.

6
00:02:01.750 --> 00:02:05.670
P-Please wait one moment! 
I'm a friend of Tayama-san's!

7
00:02:05.670 --> 00:02:10.170
She invited me to smoke here when I was 
walking around looking for a smoking area.

8
00:02:10.170 --> 00:02:14.550
I've been taking her up 
on her offer ever since...

9
00:02:15.890 --> 00:02:16.840
Eek!

10
00:02:17.850 --> 00:02:19.810
Who the heck is "Tayama"?

11
00:02:20.430 --> 00:02:23.060
Wait, now that I look at him,

12
00:02:23.060 --> 00:02:27.810
he's that gaffer who always lines up 
at Yamada's register with a smile.

13
00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:32.320
I recognize him because he resembles 
my family dog, but...

14
00:02:32.320 --> 00:02:33.440
"Tayama"?

15
00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:35.650
Don't you mean Yamada?

16
00:02:35.650 --> 00:02:38.950
Wh-Why would you bring Yamada-san up?

17
00:02:39.870 --> 00:02:41.790
No, I mean Tayama-san!

18
00:02:41.790 --> 00:02:44.870
The responsible girl 
wearing that cool, flashy jacket.

19
00:02:45.210 --> 00:02:48.710
She says she and Yamada-san 
are good friends.

20
00:02:49.170 --> 00:02:53.090
Oh, I see. This guy's getting played.

21
00:02:59.550 --> 00:03:02.850
So, you're here to smoke with Ya...

22
00:03:02.850 --> 00:03:05.100
Tayama again?

23
00:03:05.100 --> 00:03:08.900
Oh, no. I just had something to give her.

24
00:03:08.900 --> 00:03:10.110
A gift?

25
00:03:12.190 --> 00:03:14.610
Is she making you simp for her?

26
00:03:14.610 --> 00:03:16.240
It's a token of my appreciation!

27
00:03:16.240 --> 00:03:17.700
Uh-huh...

28
00:03:21.330 --> 00:03:24.250
Tayama should be clocking out soon.

29
00:03:24.250 --> 00:03:26.000
Do you want me to go get her?

30
00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:28.210
Oh, no, don't bother!

31
00:03:28.210 --> 00:03:31.630
I just figured I could 
hand it over if she was here.

32
00:03:32.500 --> 00:03:37.510
Sorry, could you pass this 
on to her for me?

33
00:03:37.760 --> 00:03:40.140
That should clear things up.

34
00:03:44.890 --> 00:03:47.980
I apologize for interrupting you 
during your break.

35
00:03:50.770 --> 00:03:54.110
He really does resemble my family dog.

36
00:03:54.110 --> 00:03:55.070
Beth...

37
00:03:57.190 --> 00:03:59.070
Manager.

38
00:04:07.750 --> 00:04:10.460
If you were going to smoke, 
you should've invited me.

39
00:04:17.420 --> 00:04:20.180
You're getting a talking-to, Yamada.

40
00:04:20.180 --> 00:04:21.840
Wait, why?

41
00:04:22.550 --> 00:04:25.140
You've been smoking here with 
a customer without permission.

42
00:04:29.350 --> 00:04:30.640
I would never.

43
00:04:30.640 --> 00:04:32.190
Pull the other one, Yamada!

44
00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:35.900
Don't try to lie your way out of this. 
Sasaki-kun told me about it.

45
00:04:35.900 --> 00:04:38.570
Wait, he was here?

46
00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:40.740
He just left.

47
00:04:40.740 --> 00:04:44.120
Sheesh. I nearly called the cops 
on him for trespassing.

48
00:04:45.870 --> 00:04:47.950
He said this was for "Tayama-san."

49
00:04:51.870 --> 00:04:54.500
Called it a token of his appreciation.

50
00:04:54.500 --> 00:04:56.920
You're this Tayama, right?

51
00:05:00.630 --> 00:05:05.140
Tayama and Yamada, though? 
Talk about half-assed.

52
00:05:05.140 --> 00:05:08.310
He's probably the only one that'd fool.

53
00:05:08.310 --> 00:05:11.730
You'd better not mess with that 
good-natured gaffer too much.

54
00:05:11.730 --> 00:05:14.730
Hey! Are you listening to me, Yamada...

55
00:05:15.730 --> 00:05:18.190
I told him it was no biggie...

56
00:05:30.580 --> 00:05:34.250
It's the perfect entertainment 
for these monotonous night shifts.

57
00:05:34.250 --> 00:05:35.580
I'll let them be for a bit.

58
00:05:51.730 --> 00:05:55.690
I ended up making myself 
scarce last night.

59
00:05:55.690 --> 00:05:58.980
I hope Tayama-san didn't get 
chewed out because of me.

60
00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:02.110
Don't bring a gaffer in here!

61
00:06:02.110 --> 00:06:04.740
I'm sorry for bringing a gaffer in here.

62
00:06:05.860 --> 00:06:07.410
I'm confiscating this gift!

63
00:06:07.410 --> 00:06:09.490
Please, have mercy!

64
00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:12.200
No more smoking!

65
00:06:12.200 --> 00:06:14.290
How heartless!

66
00:06:30.100 --> 00:06:34.350
I didn't think the web of melons 
would come into play here.

67
00:06:34.350 --> 00:06:36.520
I can't wait for the next volume.

68
00:06:36.810 --> 00:06:40.730
Okay, what do I read next?

69
00:06:47.740 --> 00:06:49.580
What's up, Yamada?

70
00:06:49.580 --> 00:06:51.290
Heya.

71
00:06:51.290 --> 00:06:54.160
Aren't you only on 
for the night shift today?

72
00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:57.420
Chief Maezono seemed to be having 
a hard time filling shifts,

73
00:06:57.420 --> 00:06:58.960
so I showed up anyway.

74
00:07:00.340 --> 00:07:02.710
You'd better have clocked in.

75
00:07:02.710 --> 00:07:05.050
I did. I totally did.

76
00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:07.800
Okay, good. Attagirl.

77
00:07:07.800 --> 00:07:12.810
Heck, boss. You really stopped 
smoking cigarettes, huh?

78
00:07:13.180 --> 00:07:14.180
Hmm?

79
00:07:17.560 --> 00:07:22.980
Oh, you have way more rights with these.

80
00:07:22.980 --> 00:07:26.070
And I can't be bothered 
brushing and using deodorizers.

81
00:07:28.030 --> 00:07:30.700
You're the one who taught me to, though.

82
00:07:34.370 --> 00:07:38.000
Okay, so what're you beating 
around the bush for?

83
00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.670
If you've got a question, 
spit it out already.

84
00:07:42.500 --> 00:07:47.220
It's just, you haven't told me 
if the smoking is okay yet.

85
00:07:47.220 --> 00:07:51.850
What? Oh, you mean the deal 
with the gaffer.

86
00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:57.020
Maybe you didn't call the cops 
but just disposed of him instead.

87
00:07:57.020 --> 00:07:58.850
You didn't bury him 
behind the store, did you?

88
00:07:58.850 --> 00:08:01.730
Where do you wanna be shot?
What'll it be?

89
00:08:01.730 --> 00:08:05.110
A-Anywhere but the lungs, please!

90
00:08:05.110 --> 00:08:07.110
Like heck I did!

91
00:08:07.110 --> 00:08:09.320
It went in one of your ears 
and out the other,

92
00:08:09.320 --> 00:08:12.370
but I said "don't mess with him too much."

93
00:08:12.370 --> 00:08:15.370
In other words, just keep it low-key.

94
00:08:15.660 --> 00:08:19.790
I'm willing to overlook it because it 
won't affect anybody's work at that hour.

95
00:08:19.790 --> 00:08:22.790
If I think it's gone past low-key, 
I'll put a stop to it.

96
00:08:23.880 --> 00:08:27.380
But otherwise, it's fine. 
There you have it.

97
00:08:29.170 --> 00:08:30.840
Lucky me!

98
00:08:31.590 --> 00:08:32.760
Hey, Yamada.

99
00:08:35.390 --> 00:08:38.140
You'd better tell me ASAP 
if anything happens.

100
00:08:39.230 --> 00:08:43.400
Okay, but what do you mean by anything?

101
00:08:43.690 --> 00:08:45.570
Isn't that obvious?

102
00:08:45.570 --> 00:08:49.650
Anything that gets 
the heart racing, of course.

103
00:08:51.910 --> 00:08:54.870
Okay. Be seeing ya.

104
00:09:01.370 --> 00:09:05.170
Maybe I should go in and apologize.

105
00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:08.340
All I wanted was to show my appreciation.

106
00:09:08.340 --> 00:09:11.170
Why'd I have to go and cause 
problems for her instead?

107
00:09:11.170 --> 00:09:12.050
Hey, trespasser.

108
00:09:12.050 --> 00:09:14.680
Whoa! Please forgive me!

109
00:09:15.760 --> 00:09:17.430
Wait, Tayama-san?

110
00:09:17.430 --> 00:09:20.180
What are you sneaking 
around for, Sasaki-san?

111
00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:25.110
I ran into another employee here 
the other night.

112
00:09:25.110 --> 00:09:27.440
Did you get in trouble because of me?

113
00:09:27.440 --> 00:09:29.690
Oh, that was the manager.

114
00:09:29.690 --> 00:09:31.950
The... The manager?!

115
00:09:32.740 --> 00:09:37.030
It was fine. Anyway, come on over here.

116
00:09:37.030 --> 00:09:38.950
Wait, what?

117
00:09:38.950 --> 00:09:42.710
D-Did your manager say 
I was allowed to smoke here?

118
00:09:42.710 --> 00:09:45.710
She said to keep it low-key, 
so it's all good.

119
00:09:45.710 --> 00:09:47.340
Low-key?

120
00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:50.710
Is that okay or not?

121
00:10:08.860 --> 00:10:10.730
Also, Sasaki-san.

122
00:10:12.740 --> 00:10:15.070
This is really cute.

123
00:10:17.240 --> 00:10:21.330
I figured you didn't want reimbursement, 
but I did want to give my thanks.

124
00:10:21.750 --> 00:10:24.000
I'm glad you like it.

125
00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:24.870
I do.

126
00:10:28.380 --> 00:10:32.260
Looking at this thing makes me smile.

127
00:10:32.260 --> 00:10:34.260
Does it, now?

128
00:10:34.260 --> 00:10:38.050
Because I can picture you 
picking it out at the store.

129
00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:43.310
Wait, why would that make you smile?

130
00:10:43.310 --> 00:10:46.810
I mean, it can't have been 
easy to find this thing.

131
00:10:46.810 --> 00:10:50.020
They don't sell a lot of 
cute ashtrays like it.

132
00:10:57.530 --> 00:11:01.620
I can imagine you had to ask people 
where they were selling these,

133
00:11:02.290 --> 00:11:05.290
and because the trinket sections 
are always full of women,

134
00:11:05.290 --> 00:11:10.960
you would've felt all awkward as you 
stood there picking a good one out.

135
00:11:15.050 --> 00:11:18.090
Tayama-san, you really can 
read minds, can't you?

136
00:11:25.100 --> 00:11:30.060
Anyway, picturing all that 
puts a smile on my face.

137
00:11:31.230 --> 00:11:34.690
Are you sure you don't just see 
this geezer as entertainment?

138
00:11:34.690 --> 00:11:38.570
What? I don't. It genuinely 
makes me feel better.

139
00:11:39.360 --> 00:11:42.330
I can never tell if she's 
being serious or not.

140
00:11:51.380 --> 00:11:52.590
Thanks.

141
00:11:53.670 --> 00:11:54.880
I'll cherish it.

142
00:11:58.430 --> 00:12:01.340
I guess it's fine either way.

143
00:12:01.340 --> 00:12:03.050
Hey, Sasaki-san.

144
00:12:03.850 --> 00:12:06.350
You should probably ash that.

145
00:12:07.350 --> 00:12:09.100
Oh, you're right.

146
00:12:09.730 --> 00:12:11.610
Go ahead and use this.

147
00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:16.150
Sure is handy, huh? Thanks...

148
00:12:18.400 --> 00:12:20.110
Th-That's kind of close.

149
00:12:20.490 --> 00:12:23.120
We don't want you getting a burn.

150
00:12:23.830 --> 00:12:24.870
So here.

151
00:12:25.580 --> 00:12:26.500
Come on.

152
00:12:26.870 --> 00:12:28.910
U-Uh...

153
00:12:28.910 --> 00:12:32.130
C-Can you just hand it to me?

154
00:12:32.130 --> 00:12:34.500
Okay, go ahead and take it.

155
00:12:36.380 --> 00:12:37.670
What...

156
00:12:38.130 --> 00:12:40.800
A bit more. Almost there.

157
00:12:45.600 --> 00:12:46.890
Tayama-san...

158
00:12:47.390 --> 00:12:49.680
Why are you moving it away?

159
00:12:49.680 --> 00:12:52.150
Oh, sorry about that.

160
00:12:52.940 --> 00:12:55.520
Sasaki-san, you've got some long arms.

161
00:12:55.520 --> 00:12:57.650
Give it to me, Tayama-san.

162
00:12:57.650 --> 00:13:00.650
Before my arm gives out.

163
00:13:03.160 --> 00:13:06.580
Ow... Ouch!

164
00:13:06.580 --> 00:13:07.330
Huh?

165
00:13:13.250 --> 00:13:14.670
A compress?

166
00:13:15.500 --> 00:13:16.920
Don't tell me...

167
00:13:20.090 --> 00:13:21.300
Are you okay?

168
00:13:21.300 --> 00:13:25.800
I'm fine. I just choked a little.

169
00:13:25.800 --> 00:13:29.220
I'm really sorry, okay?

170
00:13:29.220 --> 00:13:32.940
You don't have to apologize, Yamada-san.

171
00:13:33.270 --> 00:13:37.110
Old man cramps last for days, huh?

172
00:13:38.400 --> 00:13:40.940
Forgive me, Sasaki-san.

173
00:13:41.360 --> 00:13:42.820
I-It's okay!

174
00:13:43.320 --> 00:13:45.070
It's all right, Yamada-san!

175
00:13:45.070 --> 00:13:45.990
I'm so sorry.

176
00:13:45.990 --> 00:13:47.910
Don't be! Please don't be!

177
00:13:47.910 --> 00:13:50.580
Please stop apologizing!

178
00:13:48.950 --> 00:13:51.330
No, I must apologize.

179
00:13:50.580 --> 00:13:52.960
You haven't done anything wrong!
